1	Use Case [#5]: [Book an Appointment]

1.1	Description
The Customer wants to book an appointment on the website.

1.2	Level
Sub-function

1.3	Trigger
The Customer clicks the ‘book’ button.

1.4	Primary Actor
The customer.

1.5	Additional/Supporting Actors
Business admin

1.6	Stakeholders 
Employees
Other Customers

1.7	Preconditions
The customer must have logged into their account and selected a specific service.

1.8	Main Success Scenario
1.	Customer chooses a service.
2.	Application checks slots for availability and readies them for selection.
3.	Customer selects date/time slots.
4.  Customer selects the number of service receipts.
5.	Customer submits the booking request.
6.	Execute: Process Appointment - use case.


1.9	Extensions
1.	Exception: No booking slots available:
1.	Application warns user to try again next day

1.10	Post Conditions
1.10.1	Success End Condition
The customer receives appointment confirmation after processing of the request. 


1.10.2	Minimal Guarantees
Business admin will try fit customer into their schedule with a change of date if theur chosen date/time slot is booked by another user first
1.10.3	Failure End Condition
The booking request is not submitted to the business admin.

1.11	Frequency
Frequent.

1.12	Special Requirements
1.12.1	Performance
The booking request form should only take a minimum of 15 seconds to complete.

1.12.2	Security
Customer booking details will be sent to their email

1.12.3	Usability / Accessibility
Customer must be able to view page in English.

1.12.4	Other
1.13	Issues and Next Steps

